Greece has been embroiled in a row over [abusive migrant
detentions](http://www.hrw.org/en/news/2009/10/12/greece-escalating-risks-
migrants-unaccompanied-children) and the lip service paid so far by the new
socialist government to honor its pledges to reform the police. Two days
before the [International Day for the Elimination of Violence against
Women](http://www.un.org/Depts/dhl/violence/), an incident of police brutality
against a migrant mother and her child in Athens caused an uproar that have
triggered new government promises for police reform.

Photojournalist and blogger _Craig Wherlock_ [translated from reports in Greek
media](http://teacherdudebbq.blogspot.com/2009/11/greek-police-accused-of-
beating-35-year.html):

> a 35 year old Armenian woman was beaten, handcuffed and detained in front of
> her two year old child [..] in Athens last Thursday [..] When she went to
> get the pushchair carrying her child they grabbed her, pushed her to the
> ground, kicking and punching her in the belief she was resisting arrest. The
> hapless mother was handcuffed and taken with her child to the Aghios
> Panteleimonos police department where she was kept for four hours.

The incident was promptly [reported on Twitter by
_Cyberela_](http://twitter.com/Cyberela/status/5972634639):

> «Νταήδες» αστυνομικοί ξυλοκόπησαν 35χρονη <http://www.enet.gr/104685> (via
> @[enetgr](http://twitter.com/enetgr))
> @[chrisochoidis](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis) Τί θα κάνετε γι αυτό;

Police “bullies” assaulted a 35 year old woman <http://www.enet.gr/104685>
(via @[enetgr](http://twitter.com/enetgr))
@[chrisochoidis](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis) what are you going to do
about it?

Citizen Protection minister Michalis Chrisochoidis was harangued by demands to
take action. On Twitter
_[vivian_e](http://twitter.com/vivian_e/status/5973033954)_ said:

> @[chrisochoides](http://twitter.com/chrisochoides) Υπουργέ, δεν πάει άλλο η
> κατάσταση με την αστυνομική βία. Πρέπει να υπάρξουν παραδειγματικές
> τιμωρίες. Άμεσα

@[chrisochoides](http://twitter.com/chrisochoides) Minister, it's gone far
enough with police violence. Exemplary punishments must be handed out.
Immediately

Half an hour after the first tweet, the minister's office [responded directly
to citizens for the first time through
Twitter](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis/status/5973039969):

> @[Cyberela](http://twitter.com/Cyberela)
> @[diakoptis](http://twitter.com/diakoptis)
> @[teacherdude](http://twitter.com/teacherdude)
> @[asteris](http://twitter.com/asteris)
> @[magicasland](http://twitter.com/magicasland) μετά την καταγγελία της
> 36χρονης η ΓΑΔΑ διέταξε Ένορκη Διοικητική Εξέταση

@[Cyberela](http://twitter.com/Cyberela)
@[diakoptis](http://twitter.com/diakoptis)
@[teacherdude](http://twitter.com/teacherdude)
@[asteris](http://twitter.com/asteris)
@[magicasland](http://twitter.com/magicasland) after charges brought by the 36
year old, police HQ ordered a juried investigation to be made

… to which vivian_e [responded](http://twitter.com/vivian_e/status/5973066530)

> @[chrisochoidis](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis) Θα σας ρωτάμε κάθε μέρα
> για την πορεία της ΕΔΕ.

@[chrisochoidis](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis) we'll be querying you every
day on the progress of the investigation

Later, the minister
[announced](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis/status/5975785506) that the
officers responsible for the incident would be permanently dismissed, and
[initiated a public
consultation](http://twitter.com/chrisochoidis/status/6002431658) for the
creation of a special office to monitor incidents of police abuse.

